{
  "texts": [
    "The performance of traditional ML models is relatively unsatisfactory as that of DL algorithms.",
    "Similarly, Islam and Zhang (2018) proposed a DCNN using brain MRI data for AD diagnosis.",
    "InceptionV4 and ResNet are developed as baseline DCNNs, and their architectures are tweaked to categorize 3D brain MRI data.",
    "The implementation is carried out on a Linux machine equipped with an GeForce NVIDIA GTX 770 GPU, AMD A8 CPU, and 16GB RAM.",
    "With an accuracy of 93.18%, the model accurately diagnoses AD in its early stages."
  ]
}